				\begin{document}$${\mathrm {ring}}\;{\mathrm {width}}\;{\mathrm {index}}_t = \ln \left( {{\mathrm {precip}}} \right)_t \times {\mathrm {database}} + {\mathrm {tmax}}_t \times {\mathrm {database}},$$\end{document}ringwidthindext= lnprecipt×database+tmaxt×database,where t is the year, tmax is the average of the two dry season temperature time series, and “database” is either the factor FIA or ITRDB. Randomly subsampling the time series data underlying the ITRDB regional chronology to equal the FIA sample size of 2926 time series (100 times) resulted in explained variance and regression slopes that were essentially unchanged (SD of 0.005 (R2) and 0.002 (regression slopes) among the 100 replicates).
